        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "RFC addendum: hosted feed trust verification series",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a trust-verification addendum to RFC 0009 for the next hosted-feed series.\n\nThe addendum records the boundary established by the first implementation series: hosted feed transport, cache, refresh, entries, and diagnostics are landed, but persisted hosted feed bodies remain inert cache material until source profiles and feed trust rules explicitly validate them.\n\n## Proposed implementation series\n\n1. RFC addendum\n2. Envelope and verifier primitives\n3. Source-profile trust config\n4. Marketplace refresh trust state\n5. CLI and operator visibility\n\n## ClawHub account feeds\n\nThis revision also adds the ClawHub-owned user/publisher feed concept:\n\n- ClawHub can publish account-backed feeds tied to stable ClawHub account or publisher ids.\n- OpenClaw can trust those feeds as ClawHub-authored after feed verification.\n- Following a ClawHub account is a discovery and notification signal for new skills/plugins.\n- Following does not imply official status, Microsoft registry inclusion, install eligibility, tenant approval, or scan bypass.\n- Downstream registries can subset ClawHub account/feed state and still run their own scans and approval checks.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Reuses existing OpenClaw trust patterns: local trust anchors, fail-closed verification, bounded diagnostics, and package-source artifact verification remaining with npm, ClawHub, Git, or future skill installers.\n- Defers install authority, search ranking authority, regional selection, enterprise composition, and tenant/admin policy behavior until later PRs consume verified feed state.\n- Separates feed source trust, publisher identity, official status, registry inclusion, and install/security trust.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- checked for en dash / em dash characters in the edited RFC\n- reviewed against current OpenClaw hosted-feed and ClawHub trust patterns on `openclaw/openclaw@origin/main`",
